    "Sorting helps identify common elements more efficiently.",
    "Next, two pointers are initialized, one for each array, starting at the beginning.",
    "The algorithm then traverses both arrays in parallel.",
    "When the elements at both pointers are equal, the common element is added to the result list.",
    "If the first array's element is smaller, the pointer in that array is moved forward."
